{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480327","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480327"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:41:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:41:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"40"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/40"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.65,0.01,0.13,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"40"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53028"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/40"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"40"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38439"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"379"},{"type":"tags","id":"1984"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"4966"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"983"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9888"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11095"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11519"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13136"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19929"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33812"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38848"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41967"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44322"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44914"},{"type":"contributions","id":"47935"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/53028"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise well 55-year-old woman presents with a five-day history of right sided weakness of her face. On examination, the following findings are noted on attempting to smile (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No treatment required","Prednisolone and acyclovir","Betamethasone diproprionate lotion","Acyclovir","Prednisolone"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s combination of acute onset, unilateral, lower motor neuron weakness of the facial nerve with an erythematous and vesicular rash over the ear is consistent with herpes zoster oticus (Ramsay Hunt syndrome). When diagnosed and treated early, there is a high rate of recovery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECorticosteroids (e.g.\u003Cstrong\u003E prednisolone\u003C/strong\u003E)\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Ehave been extensively validated in well-designed trials and shown via meta-analysis to reduce the rate of residual facial nerve dysfunction by a third (5).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, the combination of corticosteroids and antivirals (e.g.\u003Cstrong\u003E prednisolone and acyclovir\u003C/strong\u003E) may reduce the late sequelae of Ramsay Hunt syndrome more compared with corticosteroids alone. Studies conducted by Monsanto have shown that combination therapy had a 93.4% improvement rate compared to 68% when only corticosteroids were administered.  Current guidelines support starting treatment with a corticosteroid if symptom onset is less than 72 hours however it should be noted that studies conducted by Crouch have shown that initiating treatment in patients as late as one week post-symptom onset is still helpful. Therefore \u003Cstrong\u003Eprednisolone and acyclovir\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate answer. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo treatment\u003C/strong\u003E is unlikely to be in the best interest of the patient. Starting treatment in the first week correlates with the highest rate of improvement, although treatment started later still appears to have some benefit. Treatment started within 72 hours after the symptom onset yields better chances of complete recovery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo date, there is no evidence to suggest that \u003Cstrong\u003Eoral antiviral therapy (e.g. acyclovir) \u003C/strong\u003Ealone is effective for the management of Ramsay Hunt Syndrome and all active treatments involve the use of corticosteroids.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBetamethasone diproprionate lotion\u003C/strong\u003E is a topical steroid used to treat a plethora of skin conditions including eczema and psoriasis but is not routinely used in Ramsay Hunt syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ramsay Hunt syndrome is a rare complication of herpes zoster, in which reactivation of the latent varicella-zoster virus in the geniculate ganglion affects the facial nerve (CNVII) and most cases will resolve spontaneously within a few weeks.","Treatment should ideally be started within 72 hours, however it is still helpful up to 7 days from symptom onset."],"references":["Jeon Y, Lee H. Ramsay Hunt Syndrome. J Dent Anesth Pain Med. 2018; 18:333-37.","Monsanto RD, Bittencourt AG, Bobato Neto NJ, Beilke SC, Lorenzetti FT, Salomone R. Treatment and prognosis of facial palsy on Ramsay Hunt syndrome: results based on a review of the literature. International archives of otorhinolaryngology. 2016 Oct;20:394-400.","Kinishi M, Amatsu M, Mohri M, Saito M, Hasegawa T, Hasegawa S. Acyclovir improves recovery rate of facial nerve palsy in Ramsay Hunt syndrome. Auris Nasus Larynx. 2001 Aug 1;28(3):223-6.","da Costa Monsanto R, Bittencourt AG, Neto NJB, et al. Treatment and Prognosis of Facial Palsy on Ramsay Hunt Syndrome: Results Based on a Review of the Literature. Int Arch Otorhinolaryngol 2016;20:394\u2013400.","Crouch, A.E., Hohman, M.H., Moody, M.P. and Andaloro, C., 2020. Ramsay Hunt Syndrome."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38439"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"40"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16958"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16958","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16958"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4717b82a-4423-4acc-b516-9e0a5cf9d670.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/4717b82a-4423-4acc-b516-9e0a5cf9d670.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":437,"height":297}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"38439","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/38439"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-09-14T12:27:55+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-14T12:28:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"40"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"53028"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"35","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/35"}